IRS990.Desc: SPOKANE UNITED METHODIST HOMES, DBA ROCKWOOD RETIREMENT COMMUNITIES (SUMH), ASSISTS ELDERLY PERSONS, INCLUDING THOSE WHO LACK ADEQUATE FINANCIAL MEANS TO PROVIDE FOR THEMSELVES, WITH FACILITIES AND SERVICES SPECIALLY DESIGNED TO MEET THE PHYSICAL, SOCIAL, AND PSYCHOLOGICAL NEEDS OF THE AGED, AND TO CONTRIBUTE TO THEIR HEALTH, SECURITY, HAPPINESS, AND USEFULNESS IN LONGER LIVING. SUMH OPERATES IN TWO LOCATIONS OR DIVISIONS, ROCKWOOD SOUTH HILL AND ROCKWOOD AT WHITWORTH, EACH OF WHICH PROVIDES DWELLINGS, APARTMENTS, AND A HEALTH CENTER FOR RESIDENTS. DURING THE YEAR ENDED MAY 31, 2022, SUMH SERVED 616 RESIDENTS AND PROVIDED 218,779 DAYS OF RESIDENT SERVICES TO AGING ADULTS. 16,780 OF THESE DAYS RELATED TO SKILLED NURSING CARE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATION IS QUALIFIED AS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 501(C)(3). ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAX IS NECESSARY. THE CORPORATION EVALUATES UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS WHEREBY THE EFFECT OF THE UNCERTAINTY WOULD BE RECORDED IF THE OUTCOME WAS CONSIDERED PROBABLE AND REASONABLY ESTIMABLE. AS OF MAY 31, 2022 AND 2021, THE CORPORATION HAD NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS REQUIRING ACCRUAL.

THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF SUMH IS ACTIVELY INVOLVED IN THE APPLEWAY COURT 202 AND APPLEWAY COURT II AFFORDABLE HOUSING PROJECTS. THE AFFORDABLE HOUSING PROJECTS FURTHER SUMH'S PURPOSES BY PROVIDING RESIDENTIAL LIVING UNITS TO ELDERLY PEOPLE WHO LACK ADEQUATE FINANCIAL MEANS TO PROVIDE FOR THEMSELVES.

THE COMPOSITION AND QUALIFICATIONS OF THE GOVERNING BODY'S VOTING MEMBERS WERE UPDATED DURING THE FISCAL YEAR AS FOLLOWS: CREATE AN IMMEDIATE PAST BOARD CHAIR POSITION. THE IMMEDIATE PAST BOARD CHAIR SHALL BE PERMITTED TO SERVE IN THIS CAPACITY FOR ONE YEAR EVEN IF HE/SHE HAS REACHED THE MAXIMUM TERM LIMIT. EMPLOYEES SHALL NOT BE ELIGIBLE TO SERVE AS BOARD MEMBERS. OFFICERS OF SUMH MAY NOT ALSO BE RESIDENTS AT SUMH. COMMITTEE CHAIRS MUST BE A BOARD MEMBER AND MAY NOT BE A RESIDENT.

A COPY OF THE 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE CFO, WHO REVIEWS THE FORM, SCHEDULES, AND RELATED ATTACHMENTS. ANY COMMENTS OR QUESTIONS ARE ADDRESSED WITH THE PREPARER AND A REVISED DRAFT IS DISTRIBUTED TO THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES. THE TRUSTEES ARE THEN GIVEN TIME TO SEND IN COMMENTS AND QUESTIONS. ONCE THE BOARD AND MANAGEMENT ARE SATISFIED WITH THE 990, THE CFO SIGNS THE FORM 8879-TE AUTHORIZING THE PREPARER TO E-FILE THE RETURN.

THE ORGANIZATION ANNUALLY DISTRIBUTES A COPY OF ITS CONFLICTS OF INTEREST POLICY FOR THE BOARD MEMBERS TO REVIEW, DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS, AND SIGN. IN ADDITION, ALL EMPLOYEES, OFFICERS, AND MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES ARE OBLIGATED TO DISCLOSE IN WRITING TO THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER OR THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES THE NATURE AND EXTENT OF ANY DIRECT OR INDIRECT INTEREST ANY SUCH PERSON OR ANY MEMBER OF HIS OR HER IMMEDIATE FAMILY HAS IN ANY ENTITY DOING BUSINESS WITH THE CORPORATION OR HAVING ANY FINANCIAL INTEREST IN ANY DEALINGS WITH THE CORPORATION. THE BOARD'S GOVERNANCE COMMITTEE MONITORS AND ENFORCES COMPLIANCE BY REQUESTING AN AD HOC COMMITTEE TO REVIEW ANY CONFLICTS AND PRESENT A RESOLUTION TO THE BOARD.

THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES USES DATA FROM THE COMPILATION OF 990S OF OTHER ENTITIES IN THE SAME AND SIMILAR INDUSTRIES TO DETERMINE THE CEO'S COMPENSATION. THE BOARD'S EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IS IN CHARGE OF THIS PROCESS AND MAKES THE FINAL DECISION ON THE CEO'S COMPENSATION. THE BOARD AS A WHOLE THEN REVIEWS THIS DECISION.

THE CEO USES THE ORGANIZATION'S BUDGETING PROCESS AND THE COMPILATION OF 990S OF OTHER ENTITIES IN THE SAME AND SIMILAR INDUSTRIES TO DETERMINE THE CFO AND SECRETARY COMPENSATION. THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES MUST THEN GIVE FINAL APPROVAL OF THE BUDGET, WHICH INCLUDES THE CFO AND SECRETARY COMPENSATION.
SUMH MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
